doc_summary_long: The IMF said tax theory suggested there should be 'significantly higher' tax rates for those on higher incomes but the argument against doing so was that hitting the rich would be bad for growth. Corbyn and the shadow chancellor, John McDonnell, said the proposed changes were needed to arrest rising income inequality - a line of argument supported by the IMF study. But between 1995 and 2010, income tax systems failed to respond to the continuing increase in inequality.
doc_summary_short: The IMF said tax theory suggested there should be 'significantly higher' tax rates for those on higher incomes but the argument against doing so was that hitting the rich would be bad for growth.
doc_title: IMF: higher taxes for rich will cut inequality without hitting growth
